Cotton South Africa Reduces Crop Forecast by 2% to 88,316 Bales on Yields

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-09-02T10:08:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/cotton-south-africa-reduces-crop-forecast-by-2-to-88-316-bales-on-yields.html
Cotton  South Africa , an industry
body, cut its forecast for the amount of the fiber its members
will produce this season by 2 percent to 88,316 lint bales.  Of that, 4,000 bales will come from Swaziland and the rest
from South Africa, the Pretoria-based group said in an e-mailed
statement today.  A  bale weighs 200 kilograms (441 pounds).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  